  <channel>
    <title>Women and Girls contributor: Madhumita Pandey</title>
    <description>Madhumita Pandey is a doctoral candidate in the Department of Criminology at Anglia Ruskin University, Cambridge. Her research is based in Tihar Central Jail, New Delhi and includes narratives of convicted rapists as well as convicted murderers to explore various cultural and gender themes in India, particularly attitudes of convicted offenders towards women. She is also a monthly columnist for the Observer, writing about mental health, child sexual health, sexual violence and social change. Her research interests include sex trafficking in India, rape myth attitudes, masculinity ideology and children of prisoners.
</description>
